<body class="blue-grey">

    {{> sidebar}}

    <a class="btn-floating btn-primary button-collapse btn-large waves-effects waves-light" data-activates="slide-out">
        <i class="large material-icons">menu</i></a>

    <nav class='blue-grey darken-1' id='trail'>
        <div class='nav-wrapper'>
            <div class='col s12'>
                <a href='/commands' class='breadcrumb'>Commands</a>
                <a href='#' class='breadcrumb'>Settings</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <header class="page-header">

        <h1 class="centre">
            Settings
        </h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <style>
            .badge::after {
                content: "" !important;
            }
            
            .string {
                background: #5B4564 !important;
            }
            
            .bool {
                background: #45644F !important;
            }
            
            .int {
                background: #456460 !important;
            }
        </style>
        <div class="section">
            <div class='row'>
                <div class='col s12 m10 l8 offset-l2 offset-m1'>
                    <p>blargbot has several configuration keys that you can use to customize your experience. You set these
                        with the following command:</p>
                    <pre><code>b!settings set &lt;key&gt; &lt;value&gt;</code></pre>
                    <p>All settings keys are case insensitive.</p>
                    <p>Additionally, variables can be of three different types.</p>
                    <h3>Variable Types</h3>
                    <p>Variables can be <code>strings</code>, <code>ints</code>, and <code>bools</code>.</p>
                    <h4>strings</h4>
                    <p>A string is just a set of letters.</p>
                    <h4>ints</h4>
                    <p>An int is simply an integer: a number without a decimal.</p>
                    <h4>bools</h4>
                    <p>A bool is just "true" or "false". You can also use 1 for true, and 0 for false.</p>
                    <h3>Keys</h3>
                    <ul class="collection z-depth-3">
                        {{#each botsettings}}
                        <li class="collection-item {{this.type}}">
                            <h4>{{this.name}}
                                <span class="new badge">{{this.type}}</span>
                            </h4>
                            <p>Key: {{this.key}}</p>
                            <p>{{this.desc}}</p>
                        </li>
                        {{/each}}
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>


        </div>


        <!-- Menu Toggle Script -->
        <script>
            init();
        </script>
    </main>
